headline: After 50 Years, Kansas City Breaks Through
abstract: The Chiefs came back to beat the Titans and the 49ers crushed the Packers. The matchup is set for Super Bowl LIV.
lead_paragraph: The Tennessee Titans were lovable underdogs, but their luck ran out on Sunday against the Kansas City Chiefs, who beat them, 35-24. The Green Bay Packers found some balance on offense in their first season under Coach Matt LaFleur, but they were crushed by the San Francisco 49ers, 37-20, in a game that was nowhere near that close. The Chiefs and the 49ers will now face off in Super Bowl LIV on Feb. 2 in Miami Gardens, Fla., in a matchup between one team with an electric passing game and one that relies on its defense and running the ball.
